{
  "info": {
    "name": "FoodBridge API",
    "description": "FoodBridge — CSE309 Software Engineering.\n\nA REST API built with FastAPI. Every functional requirement from docs/13-functional-requirements.md has an endpoint here.\n\nHOW TO USE\n1. Start the backend:  python -m uvicorn app.main:app --reload\n2. Open '2. Authentication' > 'Login (donor)' and press Send.\n   The token is captured automatically — you do not paste it anywhere.\n3. Every other request is now authorised. Run them in order.\n\nVARIABLES\n  base_url      http://127.0.0.1:8000\n  access_token  set automatically by any Login request\n  listing_id    set automatically by 'Create listing'\n  request_id    set automatically by 'Submit request'\n",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [
      {
        "key": "token",
        "value": "{{access_token}}",
        "type": "string"
      }
    ]
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "base_url",
      "value": "http://127.0.0.1:8000",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "access_token",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "user_id",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "listing_id",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "request_id",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "1. Health",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Root",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": []
            },
            "description": "Confirms the API is running. No token needed."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "OpenAPI docs",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/docs",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "docs"
              ]
            },
            "description": "The interactive documentation FastAPI generates from the code itself."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "2. Authentication (FR1, FR2)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Register a new user",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/auth/register",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "auth",
                "register"
              ]
            },
            "description": "FR1 — User Registration.\n\nCreates an account and returns a JWT immediately, so the user is signed in without a second round trip. The password is hashed with bcrypt before storage; the plain text is never written anywhere.",
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Test Restaurant\",\n  \"email\": \"test.restaurant@foodbridge.org\",\n  \"password\": \"Testing123\",\n  \"role\": \"DONOR\",\n  \"phone\": \"01700000000\",\n  \"organization\": \"Test Restaurant Ltd\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "// Save the access token so every other request can use it automatically.",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200 || pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "    const data = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('access_token', data.access_token);",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('user_id', data.user_id);",
                  "    console.log('Signed in as ' + data.email + ' (' + data.role + ')');",
                  "}",
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Login (donor)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/auth/login",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "auth",
                "login"
              ]
            },
            "description": "FR2 — User Login.\n\nRUN THIS FIRST. The test script saves the returned token into the collection variable {{access_token}}, which the collection-level Bearer auth then attaches to every other request.\n\nNote the deliberate design choice: an unknown email and a wrong password return the identical 401 message, so an attacker cannot use this endpoint to discover which addresses are registered.",
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"donor@foodbridge.org\",\n  \"password\": \"Donor123\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "// Save the access token so every other request can use it automatically.",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200 || pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "    const data = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('access_token', data.access_token);",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('user_id', data.user_id);",
                  "    console.log('Signed in as ' + data.email + ' (' + data.role + ')');",
                  "}",
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Login (recipient)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/auth/login",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "auth",
                "login"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Sign in as a recipient instead. Use this before running the 'Submit request' call, since only recipients may request food.",
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"recipient@foodbridge.org\",\n  \"password\": \"Recipient123\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "// Save the access token so every other request can use it automatically.",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200 || pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "    const data = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('access_token', data.access_token);",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('user_id', data.user_id);",
                  "    console.log('Signed in as ' + data.email + ' (' + data.role + ')');",
                  "}",
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Login (admin)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/auth/login",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "auth",
                "login"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Sign in as the administrator. Required for anything in folder 6.",
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"admin@foodbridge.org\",\n  \"password\": \"Admin123\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "// Save the access token so every other request can use it automatically.",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200 || pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "    const data = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('access_token', data.access_token);",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('user_id', data.user_id);",
                  "    console.log('Signed in as ' + data.email + ' (' + data.role + ')');",
                  "}",
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Login — wrong password (401)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/auth/login",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "auth",
                "login"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Demonstrates the failure path. Expect 401 Unauthorized with the same generic message as an unknown email.",
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"donor@foodbridge.org\",\n  \"password\": \"wrongpassword\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Who am I",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/auth/me",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "auth",
                "me"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Returns the signed-in user. The id is read from the JWT, never from the request, so this can only ever describe the caller."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Refresh access token",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/auth/refresh",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "auth",
                "refresh"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Exchanges the httpOnly refresh cookie for a new short-lived access token. The frontend calls this silently when a request comes back 401."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Logout",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/auth/logout",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "auth",
                "logout"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Revokes the refresh token server-side and clears the cookie."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "3. My profile (FR11)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Update my details",
          "request": {
            "method": "PUT",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/auth/me",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "auth",
                "me"
              ]
            },
            "description": "FR11 — Manage Own Profile.\n\nOnly name, phone, and organization are accepted. Role and email are absent from the schema on purpose: if role were editable here, any user could promote themselves to ADMIN.",
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Nadia's Kitchen\",\n  \"phone\": \"01711111111\",\n  \"organization\": \"Nadia's Kitchen, Dhanmondi\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Change my password",
          "request": {
            "method": "PUT",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/auth/me/password",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "auth",
                "me",
                "password"
              ]
            },
            "description": "FR11 — Change Password.\n\nThe current password is required even though the caller is already authenticated, so a hijacked session cannot lock the owner out. On success every refresh token for the user is revoked, signing out all other devices. Returns 204 No Content.\n\nWARNING: this really does change the password. Re-run scripts/seed.py to reset the demo accounts.",
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"current_password\": \"Donor123\",\n  \"new_password\": \"Donor456\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "4. Food listings (FR3-FR6)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Browse all listings",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/food",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "food"
              ]
            },
            "description": "FR6 — Search Food Listings.\n\nExpired listings are hidden by default, since food past its collection window should not be offered."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Search listings",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/food?search=rice&food_type=COOKED&status=AVAILABLE",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "food"
              ],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "search",
                  "value": "rice"
                },
                {
                  "key": "food_type",
                  "value": "COOKED"
                },
                {
                  "key": "status",
                  "value": "AVAILABLE"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "FR6 with filters. Free-text search runs across title, description, and pickup address; food_type and status narrow it further."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "My own listings",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/food/mine",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "food",
                "mine"
              ]
            },
            "description": "A donor's own listings, including reserved and expired ones, which the public browse endpoint filters out."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Create listing",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/food",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "food"
              ]
            },
            "description": "FR3 — Create Food Listing.\n\nRequires a DONOR or ADMIN token. The donor_id is taken from the JWT, so a listing can never be created on someone else's behalf.\n\nThe test script saves the new id into {{listing_id}} for the next calls.",
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"title\": \"Vegetable biryani, 20 portions\",\n  \"description\": \"Prepared for an event that finished early. Kept hot.\",\n  \"quantity\": \"20 portions\",\n  \"food_type\": \"COOKED\",\n  \"pickup_address\": \"House 7, Road 11, Banani\",\n  \"expiry_date\": \"2026-12-31T18:00:00Z\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('listing_id', pm.response.json().id);",
                  "}",
                  "pm.test('Listing created', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(201); });"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Get one listing",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/food/{{listing_id}}",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "food",
                "{{listing_id}}"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Fetch a single listing by id, using the id saved by the previous call."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Update listing",
          "request": {
            "method": "PUT",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/food/{{listing_id}}",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "food",
                "{{listing_id}}"
              ]
            },
            "description": "FR4 — Update Food Listing.\n\nOnly the owner may edit. Any other user receives 403 Forbidden. Fields omitted from the body keep their current values.",
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"quantity\": \"15 portions\",\n  \"description\": \"Some already collected.\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Delete listing",
          "request": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/food/{{listing_id}}",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "food",
                "{{listing_id}}"
              ]
            },
            "description": "FR5 — Delete Food Listing. Owner only. Returns 204 No Content.\n\nRun this last, or the request calls below will have nothing to point at."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "5. Requests (FR7, FR8)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Submit request (recipient)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/requests",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "requests"
              ]
            },
            "description": "FR7 — Submit Food Request.\n\nSign in as a recipient first. The service rejects a donor requesting their own listing, a duplicate pending request, and any listing that is expired or already reserved.",
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"listing_id\": \"{{listing_id}}\",\n  \"message\": \"We can collect this evening. Shelter serves 40 people.\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('request_id', pm.response.json().id);",
                  "}",
                  "pm.test('Request created', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(201); });"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Requests I sent",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/requests?box=sent",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "requests"
              ],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "box",
                  "value": "sent"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "A recipient's own submissions."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Requests received",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/requests?box=received",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "requests"
              ],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "box",
                  "value": "received"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "A donor's incoming requests. Same URL as above — the box query parameter selects which side of the conversation to return."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Approve request (donor)",
          "request": {
            "method": "PUT",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/requests/{{request_id}}",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "requests",
                "{{request_id}}"
              ]
            },
            "description": "FR8 — Approve Food Request. The core business rule of the project.\n\nApproving one request does three things in a single operation:\n  1. that request becomes APPROVED\n  2. the listing moves to RESERVED\n  3. every other pending request on that listing is auto-REJECTED\n\nThe third step is what stops two organisations travelling for the same meal. Sign in as the donor who owns the listing before running this.",
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"status\": \"APPROVED\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Decline request (donor)",
          "request": {
            "method": "PUT",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/requests/{{request_id}}",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "requests",
                "{{request_id}}"
              ]
            },
            "description": "The other branch: declining leaves the listing AVAILABLE so other recipients can still request it.",
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"status\": \"REJECTED\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "6. Admin (FR9)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "List all users",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/auth/users",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "auth",
                "users"
              ]
            },
            "description": "FR9 — Manage Users. Admin only.\n\nGuarded by the require_admin dependency, which inspects the role claim inside the JWT. A donor or recipient token receives 403 Forbidden — try it and see."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Suspend a user",
          "request": {
            "method": "PUT",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/auth/users/{{user_id}}/status?is_active=false",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "auth",
                "users",
                "{{user_id}}",
                "status"
              ],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "is_active",
                  "value": "false"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Admin only. Setting is_active=false blocks that account from signing in and deletes its refresh tokens, ending any live session immediately. Nothing the user posted is deleted.\n\nPaste a real user id from 'List all users' into the URL."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Restore a user",
          "request": {
            "method": "PUT",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/auth/users/{{user_id}}/status?is_active=true",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "auth",
                "users",
                "{{user_id}}",
                "status"
              ],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "is_active",
                  "value": "true"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Reverses the suspension."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "7. Notifications (FR10)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "My notifications",
          "request": {
